<p>Thomas Jefferson coined the word <em>pedicure</em> (at least in the sense &#8220;a person responsible for pedicure&#8221;).</p>
<p>His <a href="https://founders.archives.gov/documents/Jefferson/02-01-02-0019">memorandum book</a> for February 7, 1785, reads &#8220;P[ai]d La Forest, pedicure 12f.&#8221;</p>
<p>(Thanks, Joseph.)</p>
